parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the Takata airbag recall can lead to a delay in repairing the defective airbag, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: None
as the issue is with the unavailability of parts for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel speed sensor can cause the loss of Anti-lock Braking System (ABS), Traction Control, and Cruise Control, leading to a hazardous situation on the freeway, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The ABS
Traction Control
and Cruise Control warning lights are illuminated
the vehicle goes into Limp Mode
and there is a rapid reduction of speed. In some cases
there may be uncommanded braking
erratic transmission shifting
and a loss of motive power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel speed sensor can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, illuminate warning lights, and affect the electronic stability control system, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to exceed a certain speed
the ABS warning light and other unknown warning lights illuminate
the vehicle loses motive power
the vehicle is unable to maintain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Distribution Disconnect and Delayed Recall Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed availability of parts for recall repairs can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition for an extended period, putting drivers at risk.
symptoms: Notification of recall repair
but parts are not available
manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic stability control system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS warning light and other unknown warning lights illuminate
the vehicle loses motive power
the vehicle is unable to maintain speed.
